                            threats = "<p>As reviewed in the Bi-National Recovery Plan for the Kemp's Ridley Sea Turtle (NMFS <em>et al</em>. 2011), and the Kemp's Ridley Sea Turtle 5-year Review (NMFS and USFWS 2015), the major threats to the Kemp's Ridley vary seasonally and geographically throughout their distribution and include:<br/>1)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Fisheries (bottom trawls)<br/>2)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Fisheries (top &amp; midwater trawl, demersal gillnet, hook &amp; line commercial, hook &amp; line recreational, boat strikes)<br/>3)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Fisheries (pelagic longline, demersal longline, drift &amp; sink gillnet, pot)<br/>4)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Predation<br/>5)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Cold stunning<br/>6)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Pollution, impact of marine debris<br/>7)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Climate Change<br/>8)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Illegal harvest<br/>9)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Industrial plant intake/entrainment<br/>10)&#160; Dredging<br/>11)&#160; Ecosystem alterations<br/>12)&#160; Beach vehicular traffic<br/>13)&#160; Natural catastrophes (e.g. hurricanes)<br/>14) Toxins<br/>15) Oil spills.</p>"
